latestPosts.caption:
The longest journeys start with the smallest first steps. 

Ours began in 2016 - with just 6 toxin-free products being tested with consumers in markets of Delhi. We were a passionate startup determined to make a difference for families.

Un basement waale dinon mein, we were a small but mighty team.

Bade bade sapne lekar lambe lambe hours kaam karte the hum, and the months flew by in a blur. 

From 5 people to 50 and to a 100+, we grew rapidly but never lost sight of our purpose - to spread goodness and provide Indians with the best quality personal care products, formulated for them keeping the cultural nuances in mind. 

2020 tested our grit but we emerged stronger, quite literally moving upstairs! United by vision, we worked hard and partied harder. 

We withstood challenges but our care for consumers only amplified.

Now 700+ souls strong, the Mamaearth family embarks on a new chapter. Our journey has miles to go from these humble beginnings.

It’s you - our community - who shaped our story. Your trust empowered our startup dream to touch lives.

With infinite vision, we step into the future; into our new space. The best is yet to come on this journey of care, with our consumers by our side!

Here’s to writing our next chapter together - of purpose-driven products, happy families, and a healthier planet.

From, 
Team Honasa

#newoffice #startup #milestone #entrepreneurs #goals #vision

latestPosts.caption:
From a 2-member team ➡️ 700+ employees
From a dingy basement ➡️ a 30,000 Sqft office 
From 6 products ➡️ 300+ products
From individually planting trees ➡️ 347311 trees. 
From a tiny popup ➡️ 50 stores across India!
From 1 brand to ➡️ 6 brands 

6 years ago @varunalagh and I started with a dream. A dream to create products that are honest, safe, and empower our consumers.💫

Since then, we have grown not only as individuals but as partners as well. In times of uncertainty, our values have guided us to make tough decisions with strength and comfort, knowing that we are moving in the right direction.

I’m so grateful to our consumers, our team, our suppliers, customer and all of there families for their support at every step of the way. Your love and contribution have helped us reach here and beyond.🙏♥️ 

Here’s to 6 wonderful years of Mamaearth ✨🥳

Swipe right the pictures to go through our journey from December 2016 to today. 

#MamaearthTurns6
 #anniversary

Just one more day that I get to enjoy my younger son Ayaan’s beautiful long hair before he gets his “mundan”. If you are a parent, you would know this is super emotional, so many memories and phase of your child which won’t come back. Yes I might be crying all day today 🥲 

It’s a tradition in Hindus with a deeper meaning to this ritual. 
According to Ayurveda, the ritual of mundan is believed to help regulate the body’s temperature and maintain cerebral balance, thus promoting better and healthier growth. The act of shaving the head is also thought to open the crown chakra, enhancing the body’s energy flow, which is vital for mental and physical health. Additionally, Ayurveda suggests that this practice can remove impurities and past karma, potentially improving the child’s well-being. 

Saying good byes are tough, and so is this one. Bless him with all your love and good wishes 🙏❤️

🧿🧿🧿

From whatever little I have travelled, I would say that there is nowhere as beautiful as The Lake District. 
Honestly camera and pictures don’t do justice to the natural beauty this place is, almost close to a fairly tale land with marvellous green fields, majestic lakes and the picturesque stone architecture. 

I haven’t been to @i_am.shillong yet, which seems to be a strong recommendation and on my mind whenever I am able to take time out next. What is the most beautiful destination you guys have visited, mention and let’s chat in the comments below.
